  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7041 trading between the max negative gamma at 7015 and the massive positive gamma wall at 7050, dealers are currently in a neutral hedging posture but approaching heavy selling pressure. The PIN regime with 120.5B in total GEX creates a strong mean-reverting environment where any push above 7050 will trigger aggressive dealer selling as they hedge their short calls, while dips toward 7015 will see dealer buying support. Key resistance at 7050 (12.4B) and 7100 (11.1B) form a formidable ceiling, with 7000 (8.6B) providing the primary support magnet below.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect price to get pinned between 7015-7050 with selling pressure capping upside moves.",
